Thailand Stocks: Italian-Thai, Siam Industrial Credit, Sicco

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-05-19T09:58:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/italian-thai-indorama-ventures-mcot-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 1.59, or 0.2 percent, to 1,077.5O,
gaining for the first time in four days.  Asia Fiber Pcl (AFC)  , a Thai producer of nylon yarn,
climbed 1.9 percent to 10.6 baht, extending yesterday’s 30
percent rally. The company posted net income of 36.6 million
baht ($1.2 million) in the three months ended March 31, compared
with a net loss in the same period a year earlier.  Italian-Thai Development Pcl (ITD)  , Thailand’s largest
construction company, fell 4 percent to 3.88 baht, the lowest
close since March 29. The company swung to a net loss of 207.4
million baht in the first quarter.  Siam Industrial Credit Pcl (SICCO)  , a financial company,
surged 56 percent to 6.6 baht, the most since August 1998.  Siam
Commercial Bank Pcl (SCB)   offered to buy the Siam Industrial
shares it doesn’t already own at 6.89 baht each, the lender said
in a regulatory filing today. Siam Commercial, which owns 39
percent of Siam Industrial, dropped 1.3 percent to 114 baht.
 Sicco Securities Pcl (SSEC)  , a brokerage unit of Siam
Industrial, rallied 29 percent to 1.15 baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
